n Secrets is thus to imagine the non-instrumental without casting it as a heavy ethical burden. Non-appropriation emerges not as what is difficult to do but as the path of least resistance. The book offers a valuable counterpoint to recent anti-Enlightenment revaluations of passivity that have made non-mastery and non-appropriation the fundamental task of the ethical subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362551840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625518423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625518/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles